    {
      "name": "🟣 gRPC — Tests via API Gateway (grpcurl)",
      "description": "Ces requêtes documentent les appels gRPC directs.\n\nPrérequis — installer grpcurl :\n  wget https://github.com/fullstorydev/grpcurl/releases/download/v1.9.1/grpcurl_1.9.1_linux_x86_64.tar.gz\n  tar -xf grpcurl_1.9.1_linux_x86_64.tar.gz && sudo mv grpcurl /usr/local/bin/\n\nChaque requête contient la commande grpcurl équivalente dans sa description.\nL'API Gateway fait le pont REST→gRPC, donc tous les appels REST ci-dessus testent déjà gRPC indirectement.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "31 — gRPC ProductService.GetProduct (via REST bridge)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "// Ce test valide le chemin complet : REST → API Gateway → gRPC ProductService",
            "pm.test('Status 200 — gRPC bridge OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "const body = pm.response.json();",
            "pm.test('gRPC GetProduct retourne un produit', () => {",
            "  pm.expect(body).to.be.an('object');",
            "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('id');",
            "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('name');",
            "});",
            "pm.test('gRPC champ price (float Protobuf)', () => pm.expect(body.price).to.be.a('number'));",
            "pm.test('gRPC champ stock (int32 Protobuf)', () => pm.expect(body.stock).to.be.a('number').and.satisfy(n => Number.isInteger(n)));",
            "console.log('gRPC ProductService.GetProduct ✅ — produit:', body.name, '|', body.price, 'DT');",
            "// Commande grpcurl équivalente (exécuter dans un terminal) :",
            "// grpcurl -plaintext -import-path ./proto -proto product.proto \\",
            "//   -d '{\"product_id\": \"p1\"}' localhost:50051 product.ProductService/GetProduct"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{BASE_URL}}/products/p1",
            "description": "Teste gRPC ProductService.GetProduct via le pont REST→gRPC de l'API Gateway.\n\nCommande grpcurl directe :\ngrpcurl -plaintext -import-path ./proto -proto product.proto \\\n  -d '{\"product_id\": \"p1\"}' localhost:50051 product.ProductService/GetProduct"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "32 — gRPC ProductService.SearchProducts (via REST bridge)",
